        <mxCell id="PvKUx7To6KxHUwexcF6m-27" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;" value="Orders&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;orderId , buy/sell price , Timestamps , quantity , status , bse/nse , order type - These details need to be very high consisitency , but also ever increasing data so need horizontall scalling . So Would go with NoSQL document based DB like MongoDB&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space: pre;&quot;&gt;&#x9;&lt;/span&gt;2. Watchlilst - userId , stockId , watchListId - Schema are fixed , and&amp;nbsp; data would also not very huge so would go with SQL database .&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="230" width="510" x="50" y="1420" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="PvKUx7To6KxHUwexcF6m-29" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;" value="Capacity Estimation&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Storage Estimation&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zerodha has 16 million users on their platform&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1 Million active user who trades daily&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1 trades take 5 KB of data . stockid , orderId , price , bse/nse , user basic info , payment details .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1 user make 10 trades daily = 10 X 5 KB = 50 KB&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;For 1 million user = 1 X 10^6 X 50 X 10^3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;50 GB storage per day going to store .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;For 5 Years = 50 X 5 X 365 GB&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;100 X 10 ^ 12&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;100&amp;nbsp; TB of data for 5 years .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;There also be user data stored for 16 million user . kyc detail&amp;nbsp; , account detail , personal info . So 5 KB of data . for 16 million&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;16 X 5 X 10^9 = 80 GB extra data .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;Bandwidth Estimation&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;50 gb per day .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;1 million per day will give 11.57 ~ 12 per second .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;50 GB per day = 50 X 10 ^3 X 10 ^ 6&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;50 X 10^3 X 12&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;600 X 10 ^ 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;0.6 MB / second .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;6 hours run time only .&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Need to multiply with 4 . Ao 2.4 MB/second&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="600" x="50" y="1720" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
